# Exponential Regression

::::: {.panel-tabset}

## math

$$\begin{array}{rcl}
y & = & A(B^{x}) \\
\ln y & = & \ln A(B^{x}) \\
\ln y & = & \ln A + x\ln B \\
\end{array}$$

* response variable: log(`transistors`)
* $\beta_0 = \ln A$ and $\beta_{1} = \ln B$

## model


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
exp_fit <- lm(log(transistors) ~ year, data = moore_df)
exp_fit
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```

Call:
lm(formula = log(transistors) ~ year, data = moore_df)

Coefficients:
(Intercept)         year  
  -635.7505       0.3264  
```


